"<p><strong>What help is available?</strong></p><p>People with disabilities are "
"eligible for all <a "
"href=\"https://www.hud.gov/program_offices/public_indian_housing/programs/ph\">public "
"housing programs</a>, <a "
"href=\"https://portal.hud.gov/hudportal/HUD?src=/topics/rental_assistance\">rental "
"assistance or subsidized housing</a>, and <a "
"href=\"https://www.usa.gov/finding-home#item-37237\">Housing Choice (Section 8) "
"voucher programs</a>.</p><p><a "
"href=\"https://www.usa.gov/states-and-territories\">State and local "
"rehabilitation offices</a> may be able to assist with modifications, housing "
"counseling, and independent living skills.</p><p><a "
"href=\"https://www.usa.gov/local-governments\">Local city or county "
"governments</a> can explain any housing aid that is available to people with "
"disabilities in your area.</p><p><strong>Am I eligible?</strong></p><p>A <a "
"href=\"https://www.hud.gov/program_offices/public_indian_housing/pha/contacts\">Housing "
"Authority</a> in your area will determine your eligibility based on factors "
"including your income. Each state or city may have different eligibility "
"requirements for housing programs. Learn how to <a "
"href=\"https://www.usa.gov/finding-home#item-37252\">apply for public "
"housing</a>.</p><p><strong>Where do I call for extra help?</strong></p><p>If you "
"need extra help with your public housing application, contact your <a "
"href=\"https://www.hud.gov/program_offices/public_indian_housing/pha/contacts\">local "
"Public Housing Agency office</a> or the <a "
"href=\"https://www.hud.gov/program_offices/public_indian_housing/about/css\">Public "
"and Indian Housing Customer Service Center</a><strong>. </strong></p><p>For help "
"with other housing programs including vouchers, subsidized housing, private "
"rental housing, local programs, and other housing questions, contact a <a "
"href=\"https://www.hud.gov/i_want_to/talk_to_a_housing_counselor\">housing "
"counseling agency</a> or call toll-free (800) 569-4287.</p><p><strong>How do I "
